$ Oracle: Init parameter REMOTE_LOGIN_PASSWORDFILE
@ remote_login_passwordfile

The value of `remote_login_passwordfile` can be set to one of
table { ll
  `none` ☰ The database behaves as though there was no password file; privileged connections are not possible over nonsecure connections.
  `exclusive` ☰ The password file is exclusively used for *one* → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database.
  `shared` ☰ A password file is shared by multiple databases on the same server, or by multiple → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance[instances] of an → development/databases/Oracle/Options/real-application-clusters[RAC] database. A shared password file is *read-only*.
table }

sa:

 `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/bin/orapwd`

  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters
